MZINCHALEFT SESSION: THE ARCHIVE AND THE ESCAPE
Session Module — Picks Up in the Cognitorium

THE ELDER READING ROOM
Location: Side chamber off the archive's lower ring. The door is open. GEAR does not volunteer this room — if asked about the Cognitorium's other facilities, he'll lead them here.
THE ROOM (Read Aloud)
"Off the main archive, through a brass archway, is a smaller circular chamber. Six heavy chairs arranged in a circle, facing inward toward a central pillar. The pillar is mounted with lenses, tuning forks, and a mechanical bracket designed to hold something cylindrical — unspooling it flat, like a scroll on a reading stand.
The chairs have thick leather restraints. Wrists. Chest. Head. A metal apparatus at each headrest holds the occupant's eyes open.
The floor around the chairs is stained. The stains are old — older than anything else in the Cognitorium. They have eaten into the bronze like acid. The restraints are the most worn objects in the entire ruin. Everything else looks used once or twice. These restraints were used until the leather cracked and had to be replaced. Multiple times."
If they investigate (Guile or Magic TN 12): The bracket holds an Elder Scroll. The lenses and tuning forks record tonal frequencies produced by the reader during exposure. The restraints are sized for elves.
If they ask GEAR:
"The Optical Translation Array! Yes. The primary researchers determined early that direct Elder Scroll exposure caused irreversible neurological collapse in Dwemer subjects. Unacceptable losses.
The solution was elegant. The refugee population — the Snow Elves — provided a renewable source of biological processors. They were seated, restrained, and exposed. The Array recorded the tonal frequencies of their cognitive collapse in real-time, allowing extraction of mathematical data without researcher exposure.
The processors experienced total optic nerve destruction within 3-7 exposures, followed by progressive neurological degradation. They were then relocated to subsurface maintenance tunnels for manual labour duties until biological failure.
The data yield per unit was quite impressive."
Same chipper tone as everything else.
👁️ DAVINIA SEES: The residual intent in the chairs reads: EXTRACT. MEASURE. DISCARD. Not cruelty — utility. The faint aural residue of the victims looks like shattered glass. Cognitive signatures that were whole when they sat down and fragmented when they stood up. Thousands of readings.
CROWN REACTION: "Efficient. The instrument breaks but the data is recorded."
🎵 ORION: Diagnostic Song on the restraints — layered screaming dissonance. Not one voice. Thousands, compressed into a single chord. His ears ring for a full minute.
SAIJAH: The absence she felt in the city is absolute here. The Eldergleam's network doesn't just avoid this room. It doesn't acknowledge it exists.

THE WORKSHOP — CENTURION PRIME
Run the boss fight as written in the main module. All stats, mechanics, interactable objects, extraction rules apply.
WHEN IT POWERS DOWN
"The Centurion doesn't fall. It slows. Hammer arm drops. Legs lock. Eye dims to nothing. Steam hisses from every joint. Twelve feet of dead engineering, perfectly upright.
From a crevice in the wall, a single Spider Worker scuttles out. Ignores you. Climbs the motionless leg. Reaches the shattered chest plate. Probes the ruined hardware. Tries to tighten a broken gear. Tries to seal a venting steam pipe.
Thirty seconds.
Then it stops. Climbs back down. Retreats into the corner of the alcove."
GEAR floats over. Eye clicks on the empty chest cavity.
"Oh dear. That is suboptimal. The Primary Unit has ceased function. I will log a maintenance request."
Pause. Eye dims.
"Though I suppose no one is coming to fulfill it. Are they."
THE MATRIX
Kyboh holds it. Warm. Body temperature. Pulses like a heartbeat. Not his.
The party can catch their breath. Loot the workshop. Talk. There is no alarm. The Cognitorium is quiet.
Loot (Workshop):
Aetherial Matrix (QUEST ITEM)
Centurion Dynamo Core (Expert enchanting component)
Dwemer Metal Ingots ×4 (Tier 3 crafting)

THE PIVOT: THE DEMON CORE
Location: The Centurion Workshop. The Centurion is dead. The spider has retreated. The room is quiet.
Varon steps back from the wreckage. He holds the Aetherial Matrix in his right hand — geometric, flawless, pulsing with harsh amber light. The moment it cleared the brass housing, the air changed. Heavy. A deep vibration starts in the teeth.
The Matrix is an unshielded power core leaking raw tonal radiation.
Varon looks across the room at Kyboh. Holds it out. Doesn't say a word.
THE SPOTLIGHT
Stop. Look at Kyboh's player.
"Kyboh, the object you came here for is ten feet away. Before you take it — before anyone takes another step toward the exit — is there anything you want to do? Anything you need to prepare?"
PATH A: HE REMEMBERS THE ANCHOR
If he puts the Anchor of Stasis on before touching the Matrix: the psychic static vanishes. The Matrix's radiation is muffled. He takes it safely. Proceed to THE ALARM.
PATH B: HE FORGETS he forgot. I made bleed do full unarmed base damage.
If he takes it barehanded without the Anchor — his enchanted bones are LIVE:
"Your fingers touch the crystal. The world goes white.
The Matrix grabs the chaotic doubling enchantment in your marrow and tries to force it into a perfect loop. There is no gauntlet to channel it. There is only your flesh.
The Titan's Tithe activates. One. Two. Four. Eight. Exponential in a heartbeat. A shockwave of kinetic force explodes outward from your hands."
Kyboh: No save. 15 irreducible damage. Grey ceramic skin on his hands and forearms fractures. Bone spurs tear through at knuckles, wrists, elbows. His skeleton expands to contain the pressure.
Permanent debuff — Ossification Cascade: Unarmed strikes gain +2 damage and Bleed. But switching weapons or using items now requires a Major Action (locked, agonizing joints). Must perform nightly grinding ritual or lose multi-attacks.
Everyone within 15 feet: Hard (-4) Might save. Failure: 10 irreducible force damage, knocked Prone. Success: 5 damage, stay standing.
GEAR: "Warning! Unregulated tonal feedback! Primary Organic Designate Kyboh's skeletal resonance is engaging in uncontrolled amplification with the Matrix! Recommend immediate suppression or terminal structural detonation within 180 seconds!"
Kyboh drops the Matrix. Must scramble to get the Anchor on NOW. Once secured: silence. The Matrix can be handled safely.

THE ALARM
Trigger: The first character crosses the workshop threshold back into the Cognitorium staircase.
"The amber lamps snap to crimson. Every light in the sphere flashes from warm gold to harsh, pulsing red. A sound builds in the walls — a sustained, grinding, high-frequency vibration you feel in your teeth, in your jaw, in the bones of your hands. Every bronze pipe in the Cognitorium is screaming the same note.
Above you, heavy locks disengaging. Dozens. Simultaneously.
GEAR spins, eye clicking between red and amber.
'Safe Integration Protocol terminated. System-wide biological purge activated. All non-authorized organic material will be eradicated.'
Pause.
'That would be you. Current survival probability: 4.2%. I recommend we leave immediately.'"
👁️ DAVINIA SEES: The Cognitorium shifts from dormant blue to thrashing red intent. Every surface lit with a single directive: EXTIRPATE.

THE ESCAPE — CORE MECHANIC
THE TOLL OF 8
Every zone requires 8 Safe Passages — one for each body that needs to get through (5 PCs + Varon + Ylva + GEAR).
Each player rolls for themselves. Players can take ADDITIONAL rolls to cover NPCs or weaker party members. ("I'm rolling Might to bash a path AND Agility to drag Varon through it" = 2 rolls = 2 Safe Passages.)
Every failed roll = one catastrophic hit. If a player fails a roll meant to protect an NPC, the PLAYER takes the hit.
