PART 1: THE COGNITORIUM ASCENT
They are at the bottom of the brass sphere. They must climb the spiral staircase through the archive to the docking port at the top. Three zones. 8 Safe Passages each.

ZONE 1: THE LOWER ARCHIVE
The contrast: Hours ago, they walked these aisles in silence. Davinia read data-plates. Alfonso found the quarantine chamber. The shelves were pristine, the lamps warm, the air still.
"The archive is unrecognizable. The pristine bronze shelving is torn open — wall panels have retracted and Dwemer Spheres are unfolding into the aisles between the data-plate racks. The amber reading lamps have gone crimson. The thousands of metallic scrolls on the shelves rattle in their housings from the vibration of the alarm. The Spheres are using the stacks as cover, firing heavy crossbow bolts through the gaps between shelves."
The action: Fight through the bookshelves. Spheres fire through the stacks. The party must push from the workshop door to the base of the spiral staircase.
Roll options: davinia grabbed a book for ismara. 
Might TN 14: Shove through a shelf unit, toppling it into a Sphere
Agility TN 14: Weave through the aisles, using data-plate racks as cover
Magic TN 12: Blast a path through the shelving (destroys irreplaceable Dwemer research — Ismara notices)
Failure: The Meat Grinder — 45 physical. A Sphere catches you between two shelf units and drives a blade arm through the gap.
GEAR: "The archive's organizational system is being significantly disrupted. I am cataloguing the damage. This is deeply distressing from a data-preservation standpoint."

ZONE 2: THE SPIRAL STAIRCASE
The contrast: On the way down, they passed viewports into Blackreach and marveled at the underground continent. The staircase was quiet, lit, beautiful.
"The staircase is a kill funnel. Spheres have dropped onto the steps above you — you can hear the grinding of their treads echoing down the spiral. The viewports into Blackreach flash with crimson emergency lighting. Through the glass, you can see the entire underground city below activating — structures lighting up across the cavern in a chain reaction. What you're fighting here is a fraction of what's waking up down there.
Above you on the stairs: spinning blade arms and the heavy thunk of crossbow bolts embedding in bronze railings."
The action: Vertical push up a narrow spiral staircase against Spheres descending from above. No room to flank. No room to dodge. Pure brute-force ascent.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Shield-push up the stairs, battering Spheres back
Agility TN 14: Time the blade arm sweeps and slip between strikes
Magic TN 12: Blast the Sphere off the staircase (it falls into the archive below — satisfying, but another replaces it)
Failure: The Meat Grinder — 45 physical. Batted against the brass railing hard enough to dent it with your body.
Through the viewports: Blackreach is awake. Every Dwemer structure in the cavern below is lighting up crimson. The Cognitorium was the brain. The city below is the body. And the body just received the order to kill.

ZONE 3: THE DOCKING PORT
The contrast: The platform was waiting for them peacefully when they arrived. The hatch spiralled open. The air was warm and sterile.
"Two Spheres have secured the top of the stairs, blocking the platform. They stand shoulder-to-shoulder in the narrow corridor, blade arms extended, forming a wall of spinning bronze between you and the lift. Behind them, the docking port hatch is open — the platform visible beyond. Twenty feet of corridor. Two machines designed to kill everything that tries to cross it."
The action: Break the blockade. Get onto the 50-foot disc.
Roll options:
Might TN 16: Charge the blockade head-on, physically shove both Spheres aside
Agility TN 14: Slide under the blade arms (the gap between their torsos and the floor is JUST wide enough)
Magic TN 12: Ice wall behind the Spheres, pinning them against it while the party slips past
Failure: The Meat Grinder — 45 physical. The Sphere catches you mid-charge and drives you into the corridor wall.
GEAR at the docking port: System Override on one of the blocking Spheres. Magic TN 16: success disables it for 1 round (creating a gap). Failure: the Sphere's blade arm speeds up (+2 damage). Risk/reward.
Once all 8 passages are through: The platform activates. The docking clamp releases. The platform begins ascending into the shaft. Spheres pursue to the port edge — crossbow bolts spark off the shaft walls as the party rises out of range.

PART 2: THE DEEP LIFT — 8 PHASES
The platform launches into the 500-foot enclosed shaft. They are trapped on a 50-foot bronze disc grinding upward. 8 Safe Passages per phase. 8 phases total.
This is the endurance test. The shaft is enclosed — bronze walls sliding past on all sides. No escape. No shortcuts. The only way out is up, and up takes time.

PHASE 1: THE DROP
"The shaft is enclosed bronze, lit by crimson emergency strips. The alarm is a physical pressure in the confined space. Then — maintenance hatches in the shaft wall BANG open. Spider Sentinels drop onto the platform from above, legs splayed, static crackling."
The threat: Spiders dropping from ceiling hatches directly onto the platform. Close quarters melee.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Grab the spider mid-air and smash it into the platform floor
Agility TN 14: Dodge the drop and counterattack
Magic TN 12: Blast them off the platform edge into the shaft below
Failure: The Meat Grinder — 45 physical. A spider lands on your shoulders and drives its leg stabs into the gaps in your armor.

PHASE 2: THE VENTS
"The lift passes a section of shaft lined with exhaust vents — horizontal openings in the bronze walls, each about two feet wide. As the platform rises past them, spider legs reach out. They are inside the vents, firing Static Shock through the openings. Crossfire from both walls."
The threat: Spiders in the walls firing through narrow openings. Ranged assault from both sides simultaneously.
Roll options:
Agility TN 14: Dodge the crossfire, pressing flat against the platform
Magic TN 12: Ice-wall a vent shut / dissonant note scrambles spider inside
Might TN 12: Use a shield or improvised barrier to block the shots
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. The Static Shock hits you from two directions at once.

PHASE 3: THE BREACH
"The platform shudders. A grinding sound from below. Manipulator legs punch through the floor grating — spiders are climbing the lift mechanism itself, cutting through from underneath. The metal beneath your feet sparks and buckles."
The threat: Spiders breaching the platform floor. Sections of grating becoming hazardous.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Stomp the spider back through the grating before it fully breaches
Agility TN 14: Leap to a safe section as the floor gives way beneath you
Magic TN 12: Seal the breach with ice or force
Failure: The Crush — 35 bludgeoning + Staggered. The grating collapses under you and a spider grabs your leg, dragging you half through the floor.
GEAR: Tonal Pulse staggers every spider that has breached the surface. Buys one round of free stomping.

PHASE 4: THE BOARDERS
"The spiders from below have fully breached. A dozen machines now share the 50-foot disc with you, scuttling between your legs, sparking, stabbing. The platform has become a melee arena with no walls and a 300-foot drop on every side."
The threat: The platform is SHARED. Spiders everywhere. Fighting in close quarters with nothing to brace against.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Sweep spiders off the platform edge with a wide strike
Agility TN 14: Dance between them, kicking them toward the edge
Magic TN 12: Area blast (risks hitting allies in the close quarters — Magic TN 14 if trying to avoid friendly fire)
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. Multiple spiders discharge simultaneously into you.

PHASE 5: THE STEAM VENTS
"The lift passes ruptured thermal pipes in the shaft wall. High-pressure steam floods the shaft — scalding, blinding, filling the platform with a white-hot fog that sears exposed skin. You can't see your own hands. The spiders don't care — they don't have eyes."
The threat: Environmental. Scalding steam blinds the party. The spiders navigate by vibration and are unaffected.
Roll options:
Magic TN 14: Shield yourself and allies with a ward or ice barrier
Guile TN 14: Navigate by sound, tracking spider movements through the steam
Might TN 14: Endure the burns and fight blind
Failure: The Crush — 35 bludgeoning + Staggered. Steam scald plus a spider attack you didn't see coming.

PHASE 6: THE RAIN OF BRONZE
"From above — from the city level — a sound like hail on a tin roof. Then it's not a sound. It's OBJECTS. Hundreds of tiny, newly manufactured spider-drones are being dumped down the shaft. They fall past the platform in a curtain of sparking brass. Some land on the disc. Some bounce off. Some grab hold."
The threat: Volume. A rain of small, aggressive machines falling from above. Not individually dangerous — overwhelming in number.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Shield overhead, deflecting the rain
Agility TN 14: Dodge the falling machines, sweeping them off as they land
Magic TN 12: Create a canopy of ice or force above the platform
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. Buried under a pile of sparking, discharging mini-drones.

PHASE 7: STRUCTURAL FAILURE
"The combined weight of the boarders, the damage to the grating, and the stress of the emergency ascent exceed the platform's design tolerances. The disc TILTS. Thirty degrees, sudden, violent. Everything on the platform — spiders, people, gear — slides toward the low edge. Below that edge: three hundred feet of open shaft."
The threat: The platform itself is failing. Gravity is the enemy.
Roll options:
Might TN 16: Grab the mechanism housing at the center and hold on
Agility TN 14: Catch yourself on the grating, brace against the tilt
Might TN 12: Grab an ally who's sliding toward the edge
Failure: The Crush — 35 bludgeoning + Staggered. You slide into the platform railing hard enough to bend it. One more inch and you're falling.
GEAR: Rolls to the low edge, his tiny legs scrabbling for purchase. "The platform's structural integrity has been compromised! Estimated time to total failure: longer than our remaining ascent, I think! Probably!"

PHASE 8: THE SLAM
"The lift hits the city-level docking bay without decelerating. The mechanism was designed for controlled arrival. This is not controlled. The platform SLAMS into the housing with enough force to throw everyone off their feet. The remaining spiders on the platform are crushed between disc and dock. The impact rings through the entire city level like a bell."
The threat: Impact. Pure kinetic force.
Roll options:
Agility TN 14: Brace for impact, absorbing the shock with bent knees
Might TN 14: Plant yourself and tank it
No magic option — this is physics
Failure: The Crush — 35 bludgeoning + Staggered. Thrown across the platform, hit the docking housing, wind knocked out.
Everyone hears it now. From the corridors beyond the docking bay — the sound they heard faintly during Wave 4. Thousands of metal legs on bronze flooring. Close. Very close. A sound like heavy rain on a tin roof made of brass and electricity.

PART 3: THE DEAD CITY — THE SWARM
They step off the battered lift platform. The city they explored hours ago is a knee-deep flowing river of 11,000 repurposed Spider Workers. They must run 400 meters through the rooms they know. 5 zones. 8 Safe Passages each.

ZONE 1: THE TRANSIT HUB
The contrast: They arrived here in wonder. The platform descended through the ceiling and settled gently. The corridors branched in every direction, amber-lit, silent, welcoming.
"The transit hub is chest-deep in bronze. Thousands of Spider Workers pour through the corridors from every direction, converging on the Deep Lift docking bay. They flow over and around each other like water, legs clicking, static crackling in a continuous low buzz. The amber lamps are crimson now. The corridor ahead — the main artery to the Surface Lift, four hundred meters — is a river of machines.
You have to go through it."
The action: Break into the swarm. Form a wedge. Start moving.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Shoulder into the current, physically displacing the machines
Agility TN 14: Leap onto the bronze tide, using spider shells as stepping stones before they shift
Magic TN 12: Blast a channel into the flow
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. Pulled under the surface of the swarm. Spiders climb your legs and discharge.

ZONE 2: THE DINING HALL
The contrast: The stone tables with brass plates set for a meal that never happened. The seats arranged. The quiet dignity of a civilization that stopped mid-dinner.
"The dining hall is unrecognizable. The swarm has poured over the stone tables, knocked the brass plates to the floor, swept the set chairs aside. The meal that never happened 4,000 years ago has been destroyed in seconds by machines responding to an alarm their makers will never hear. The tables are the only surfaces above the swarm — islands of stone in a bronze sea."
The action: Cross the dining hall. The tables offer temporary high ground but the gaps between them are swarm-filled.
Roll options:
Agility TN 14: Leap from table to table, staying above the swarm
Might TN 14: Wade through the gaps, shoving machines aside between tables
Magic TN 12: Ice-bridge between table surfaces
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. You miss a jump or the table shifts under your weight. Into the swarm.

ZONE 3: THE LIVING QUARTERS
The contrast: Small, identical chambers. Made beds. Tidy rooms. The brass horse figurine on a stone pillow. Nobody packed. Nobody left.
"The corridor narrows through the living quarters. Every single open bedroom door is vomiting spiders — they pour from the chambers in horizontal waves, hitting the party from the flanks as they push forward. The made beds are buried. The tidy rooms are nests. The brass horse figurine Kyboh found is somewhere under the tide."
The action: The corridor is an ambush alley. Spiders from the front AND from every doorway on both sides.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Hold the flanks, body-blocking the doorways as the group pushes through
Agility TN 14: Sprint between doorway gaps, timing the waves
Magic TN 12: Ice-wall doorways shut as you pass them (FP per wall)
Failure: The Meat Grinder — 45 physical. Hit from the side by a horizontal wave of machines. Pinned against the opposite wall.

ZONE 4: THE FABRICATION WORKSHOPS
The contrast: Partially assembled components on benches. Precision tools on walls. Work frozen mid-task. A wrench set down by someone who went to get water and never came back.
"The workshops have become the swarm's armoury. The machines are using the environment — knocking heavy tools off benches into your path, triggering dormant fabrication equipment that slams mechanical arms across the corridor. The precision tools that sat quietly on walls are now projectiles, swept off their mounts by the flowing bronze and flung at ankle height."
The action: Navigate a corridor that is actively weaponizing itself. The machines aren't just bodies — they're using the infrastructure.
Roll options:
Agility TN 16: Dodge the swinging fabrication arms AND the floor-level swarm
Might TN 14: Smash through the triggered equipment, clearing the path
Guile TN 14: Read the mechanical patterns, timing movement between arm swings
Magic TN 12: Disable the fabrication equipment with a tonal pulse or force blast
Failure: The Crush — 35 bludgeoning + Staggered. A fabrication arm catches you across the chest. You go down into the swarm.
The sealed quarantine door: Still sealed. Still red. The swarm flows around it. Even in purge mode, the city respects a 4,000-year-old quarantine. Mention it once.

ZONE 5: THE FINAL STRETCH
The contrast: The last hundred meters of corridor before the Surface Lift transit hub. On the way down, the party walked this in amber light, commenting on the architecture, feeling safe.
"The Surface Lift is visible ahead. The transit hub opens at the end of the corridor — you can see the brass tubes, the platform, the gears. A hundred meters.
Behind you, the swarm surges. The machines know you're escaping. The floor-level flow becomes a WAVE — a tidal front of bronze rising from ankle-height to waist-height, accelerating. This is no longer a river. It's a wall of metal bearing down on you."
The action: Pure desperate endurance. Sprint for the platform.
Roll options:
Might TN 16: Outrun the wave through sheer power, driving forward
Agility TN 14: Sprint with everything you have
No magic option — just run
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. The wave catches you. You're tumbled in bronze, discharged on from every direction, and spit out at the transit hub threshold.

PART 4: THE SURFACE LIFT — 2 PHASES
They reach the final transit hub. The Surface Lift is waiting. The brass resonator tubes stand at the cardinal points. Behind them: the swarm.

PHASE 1: THE HOLD
"The transit hub opens — widest space in the city, corridors converging. The Surface Lift platform sits in the center. The four brass tubes stand exactly as you left them.
Behind you, the swarm. Filling the corridor like water in a pipe, accelerating, a wall of sparking bronze about to crash into the room.
Someone needs to play the tubes. Everyone else needs to hold that corridor."
The split:
Activator (1 character): Plays the four tubes in sequence. One tube per round. 4 rounds total. W → N → S → E. No check if they remember the sequence. If forgotten: Guile TN 10 to recall. The activator does NOT roll for Safe Passages — they are occupied.
Defenders (everyone else): Must generate 8 Safe Passages to hold the 15-foot chokepoint for 4 rounds. The swarm is trying to flood the transit hub.
Roll options for defenders:
Might TN 14: Hold the line physically, shoving the swarm back at the corridor mouth
Magic TN 12: Wall off sections of the entrance, funnelling the swarm
Agility TN 14: Rapid strikes at the leading edge, knocking machines back into the flow
Failure: The Meat Grinder — 45 physical. The swarm breaches the line. You're hit by the full force of the leading wave. Everyone on the platform also takes 5 shock + 4 FP drain from the overflow.
GEAR at the chokepoint: Tonal Pulse. The 15-foot corridor mouth concentrates every spider into his burst radius. Every spider in range Staggered for a full round. The defenders get one round of breathing room. One use. Make it count.
THE TUBES:
Tube 1 (West): Gears engage. Grinding from below.
Tube 2 (North): Platform jolts. Vibrates.
Tube 3 (South): Mechanism locks. Platform lifts one inch.
Tube 4 (East): Emergency ascent.

PHASE 2: THE LAUNCH
"The fourth note rings. The platform LAUNCHES — not the smooth descent they remember, but a violent upward catapult that throws everyone off their feet. Spiders that had reached the platform's edge are flung off by the acceleration. But some grabbed hold. Dozens of them, clinging to the grating, the railing, the underside."
The threat: The platform is rocketing upward. Spiders cling to every surface. The party must clear them while fighting the G-force.
Roll options:
Might TN 14: Pry spiders off the railing and throw them into the shaft
Agility TN 14: Keep your footing on the accelerating platform while stomping boarders
Magic TN 12: Blast the platform edges clean
Failure: The Tonal Overload — 30 shock + 15 FP drain. A cluster of clinging spiders discharges into the platform grating. Everyone touching the floor feels it.
"The platform SLAMS into its surface housing. Gears lock. Bronze doors spiral open above your heads.
Cold air. Snow. Wind."

THE SURFACE
"You stumble onto frozen ground. Snow blinding after hours of amber and crimson. Wind through sweat-soaked clothing. The bronze doors grind shut below. Locks engage. Deep, final clanks.
Nothing.
Just wind. Snow. The depression in the Pale where you started. The resonator tubes humming faintly in the wind. From the surface, nothing has changed.
Kyboh holds the Matrix."
GEAR ON THE SURFACE
GEAR rolls out behind them. Eye blinks in natural light for the first time in 4,287 years.
Very still. Very quiet.
"Surface conditions detected. Atmospheric composition: standard. Temperature: below optimal. Precipitation: frozen water crystals."
The eye rotates upward.
"I have not been above the surface level since my manufacture."
Long pause.
"Where are we going next?"

