ESCAPE GM NOTES
Calibrate to the table, not the math. 18 zones/phases × 8 passages = 144 potential rolls. That's a LOT. If the table is loving it, run every zone. If they're flagging, collapse two zones into one. The structure supports compression — merge Zone 3 and 4 of the city, skip Phase 6 of the lift. The framework is maximum; the execution is flexible.
Failure never stops progress. They WILL get out. The question is what they have left. Track HP and FP across the entire escape. A party that exits with single-digit FP across five people has a very different dragon fight than one that managed efficiently.
The contrast is the design. Every zone they pass through during the escape is a room they explored peacefully hours ago. The made beds. The set plates. The horse figurine. Name these things as they're destroyed by the swarm. The players will remember finding them. Now they're watching them get buried.
The spider fixing the Centurion gets its thirty seconds. Before the alarm. Before the chaos. Let the quiet moment breathe.
GEAR's Tonal Pulse resets per Part (Cognitorium, Lift, City, Surface Lift). Four uses total across the entire escape. He should use one per Part for maximum coverage.
The sealed quarantine door gets mentioned once during the city swarm. The swarm flows around it. Even in purge mode, the city respects a 4,000-year-old quarantine. The players will remember.
GEAR is a Chekhov's gun. He will answer any question with complete honesty including the ones that destroy the campaign's biggest secret.

