AT 60 HP — THE RETREAT
"Krosulhah snarls, black blood streaming. He drags himself toward the cliff face, claws gouging stone. One shattered wing-beat. Two. He hauls himself over the ridge and launches into the grey sky, trailing blood.
The wing-beats fade. Gone. Not dead."
No soul. No loot. Returns later.

AT 0 HP — THE KILL
"Krosulhah crashes onto the road. Amber eyes find yours. Not fear. Cold, ancient hatred.
Jaw opens. A final hiss of superheated air between fangs the length of your forearm. Then the light goes out. Jaw closes. Body settles.
Silence. Wind. Ticking of cooling stone.
The scales glow from within — amber light pushing through the cracks, brighter, brighter. The body combusts. Not fire. LIGHT. Flesh burns away. Bones blacken. A torrent of white-gold energy erupts — the dragon's soul, ripping free.
It hangs in the air. One heartbeat.
Then it moves. Not upward. Not dispersing. It streaks down the road, curving around the bend toward where Bjorn took the horses. Vanishes behind the cliff wall."

AFTER THE KILL — THE SECOND SOUL (GM EYES ONLY)
Bjorn is around the bend. Soul strikes his chest. Throws him against the cliff. Ten seconds: bones reset, muscle rebuilds, decades burn away.
After: back pain gone, stiff hands gone, visibly de-aged, broader, soldier's posture. Terrified. Composes himself before the party arrives.
👁️ DAVINIA (if watching): The light is a consciousness — not dispersing, CHOOSING. Drawn to an enormous aura around the bend. She knows it went to Bjorn. His aura afterward: doubled. Two dragon souls. Blinding.
CROWN REACTION: Nothing spoken. Crown's attention sharpens. Ismara is very interested.
WHEN THEY FIND BJORN
"He's leaning against the cliff wall. Breathing hard. He looks... different. Younger. Lines around his eyes softened. Posture straighter. Hands steady.
He won't meet your eyes.
'We need to keep moving.'"
If pressed: "I'm fine. Just the adrenaline. Can we go?"
If pressed harder: "I don't know what happened. I saw the light and then — I don't know. I don't want to talk about it. Please."
